Biography

James was born about 1819. He was the son of John Cronin. He was born in Umerabwe, parish of Boherbwe, County Cork, Ireland. James was a pioneer farmer who settled on land north of O'Neill around 1876. He came to the US about 1855 and lived with his brother, John and his family.[1] James never married.[2]

James Cronin of Rulo sued the Burlington railroad for killing his cow. The jury awarded him $25.[3]

After John died, James moved in with his niece, Mrs. C.C. McHugh.[4]

He passed away in 1892.[5]
